 :                                                                            :
 :                        i n s t a l l a t i o n                             :
 .                                                                            :
                                                                              .

 @{fg shine}To install...@{fg text}



 All you have to do is to copy the main executable file in this archive to
 whatever directory you wish. I would advice SYS:C/.


 Also, if you wish to use it together with AmiExpress v3.x+, then you should
 write a command-line into your logoff-script for each node.


 That's all... (Simple isn't it? :)




 Functionality :


   Log-shrink <Path+Filename> <Size>

   <Path+Filename> is the source-file to be shrinked.
   <Size> is a number in bytes to dedicate how big the logfile should be...



 If there is spaces in the filename, use "'s marks to indicate start and the end
 of the complete path+filename.



 Remember : This shrinker will cut from within the file -> end of file. 
            So... You won't miss your last entries in the file. :)


@endnode





